6.1 Random Generation Constraints (Anti-deadlock Design)

To ensure all generated maps are solvable and fair:

Absolute Forbidden Zones

The following positions are strictly prohibited for placing boxes or targets:

(0,0), (0,9), (9,0), (9,9)

👉 Prevents immediate deadlocks at corners

Target Protection Rule
Targets (^) cannot be placed adjacent to outer walls
Ensures at least one valid pushing direction
Box Flexibility Check

After placing each box:

It must have at least TWO adjacent empty cells
Otherwise, regenerate the position

👉 Ensures boxes are movable

Obstacle Placement Rules
Obstacles (.) cannot overlap with targets (^)
Obstacles must not block essential paths
Obstacles must not isolate boxes or targets
